             were indicted for <rs id="t18200918-263-off1506" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200918-263-off1506" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-263-off1506" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18200918-263-cd1507" type="crimeDate">16th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-263-off1506 t18200918-263-cd1507"></join>, one handkerchief, value 4 s., the goods of a certain 
                     <persName id="t18200918-263-victim2462" type="victimName">man<interp inst="t18200918-263-victim2462" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-263-off1506 t18200918-263-victim2462"></join>
                     </persName>
                   unknown, from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-263-person2463">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BIDGOOD
               <interp inst="t18200918-263-person2463" type="surname" value="BIDGOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-263-person2463" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-263-person2463" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carpenter, and live in Castle-street, Oxford-market. On the 16th of July, about nine o'clock at night, I was in the narrow part of Spring-gardens, going into the Park, and saw the prisoners together, feeling several gentlemens' pockets. They followed a gentleman along Cockspur-street, and at the corner of <placeName id="t18200918-263-crimeloc1508">Pall-mall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-263-crimeloc1508" type="placeName" value="Pall-mall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-263-crimeloc1508" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-263-off1506 t18200918-263-crimeloc1508"></join> Wright took up the skirt of his coat, and took a handkerchief out. I went up, told the gentleman, and seized them both. Matthews threw the handkerchief down, and wrested himself from me; I picked it up, called Stop thief! Gillon stopped him in my sight. The gentleman claimed the handkerchief. The gang came round, I told him to follow me to the watch-house, but he did not. I do not know his name.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-263-person2464">
                  JOSEPH 
                  GILLON
               <interp inst="t18200918-263-person2464" type="surname" value="GILLON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-263-person2464" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-263-person2464" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My father is the watch-house-keeper. I heard Bidgood cry Stop thief! saw Matthews running in the road, and secured him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-263-person2465">
                  JOHN 
                  RAYMENT
               <interp inst="t18200918-263-person2465" type="surname" value="RAYMENT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-263-person2465" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-263-person2465" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a smith. I saw Matthews running and seized him - on going up Church-passage he dropped a silk handkerchief.</p>
